Since you're reading this, you've already downloaded and uncompressed 
the sources file. So now we install. This instructions are specific
for Debian based distributions for should work for any other type.

Installation:
$sudo ./install.sh

Recommended:
It is a good idea to have the clients installed, so be sure to have the following
ones installed. Also, a very nice addition is a "dialog" menu list, so install
the package "dialog". For ubuntu, you might want to run this:

$sudo aptitude install xvnc4viewer xtightvncviewer vnc-viewer rdesktop dialog ssh-client telnet-client lftp
